</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRODERICK MURDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As an RN student who just finished my psych rotation at the county 
mental-health facility, I did not find it surprising that someone as troubled 
as Mrs. Broderick got through the system only to carry out the murders. 
</P>
<P>
A 72-hour hold on someone so disturbed is not enough. Time after time I saw 
patients released who were violent when brought in and who weren't ready to 
leave after only 72 hours. I've always wondered if the paranoid schizophrenic 
who was my case study ever got around to harming someone. The ACLU may have had 
good intentions when they overhauled the mental-health system in the 1960s, but 
they really blew it. 
</P>
<P>
SHERRY OWENS 
</P>
<P>
Riverside 
</P>
</TEXT>
