</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was saddened by Wallace's story on the Broderick marriage and its tragic 
consequences -- but not surprised. It is too bad that a woman allowed herself 
to assume complete control of rearing her children while encouraging her 
husband to be the sole financial support of the family. The duties of either of 
these roles are enough to make anyone crazy. 
</P>
<P>
CHRISTINE LOVRET STAPP 
</P>
