<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLMOS AS CROCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In reference to your July 1 Outtakes item on actor Edward James Olmos playing 
the late inger Jim Croce: Will this start a new Hollywood fad? If so, why not 
Eddie Murphy as Abraham Lincoln? John Lone as Jack Kennedy? Or Cheech and Chong 
as the Wright Brothers? Since Olmos isn't required to sing, why not save Rob 
Lowe from obscurity and cast him, with a little heavy makeup, as Sammy Davis 
Jr.? 
</P>
<P>
I guess Hollywood figured casting an Italian-American actor to play an 
Italian-American like Croce might give them the idea they could play roles 
other than Mafia dons, pimply juveniles and oversexed buffoons. 
</P>
<P>
Certainly, this would not gain Hollywood the same brownie points for its 
assumed liberalism as would choosing Mexican-American Olmos. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN PRIMAVERA 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
