<HEADLINE>
<P>
GROSS ADVANCES TO RACQUETBALL SEMIFINALS, 15-4, 15-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL WALKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Racquetball form prevailed in Canoga Park on Saturday as the three top-seeded 
players, vying for the $500 first prize in the men's open division, moved into 
the semifinals of the Summer Shootout at Sequoia Club/Racquetball World. 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks' Andy Gross, seeded No. 1, made quick work of Eric Wang of 
Chatsworth, 15-4, 15-7, and will face Dave Genevae of Yorba Linda this morning 
at 11. 
</P>
<P>
Genevae defeated Dave Owen of Studio City, 15-11, 15-9. 
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Ed Andrews of Huntington Beach struggled against Anthony Buccino 
of West Hills. Buccino took the first game, 14-15, before the veteran Andrews 
rallied to win the second, 15-2, and the tiebreaker, 11-4. 
</P>
<P>
Andrews will play Mark Silva of West Hills in another 11 a.m. semifinal match. 
Silva, seeded No. 3, came from behind and outlasted Gabe Astalos of Sherman 
Oaks in a tiebreaker, 8-15, 15-3, 11-7. BILL WALKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
