<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS HAVE THEIR SAY ON DANNEMEYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How terrible it would be if this wonderful, multifarious country were governed 
solely by the likes of William Dannemeyer, whose controlling vision encompasses 
only what suits his own needs. Posed at his tidy desk with cold eyes crinkled, 
Dannemeyer stares off into a vision of Utopian America born of an MGM back-lot 
fantasy -- a Mickey Rooney world of malt shops, town squares and manicured 
lawns that fronted perfect homes filled with well-fed, straight Caucasians. 
</P>
<P>
It's a sentimental illusion that perhaps only a white heterosexual male could 
get sentimental about. Meanwhile, the blacks, the gays, and all the others who 
only appear as noisy, amusing extras in such fantasies, have a different view 
of what's been lost and gained in this country. Dannemeyer says he sleeps at 
night. Of course he does. Anyone so out of touch would no doubt sleep like a 
baby. 
</P>
<P>
DOUGLAS SOESBE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
