<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUSSIAN 'ROOTS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhores Medvedev, in his (June 3) review of Dusko Doder's and Louise Branson's 
biography, "Gorbachev: Heretic in the Kremlin," considers it unlikely that 
Gorbachev could have had an older brother who died during World War II. 
</P>
<P>
Even if Maria Panteleevna Gorbachev did not become a teen-age mother, she could 
have had a stepson. I presume that it is correct to refer to a half-brother 
some seven years one's senior as just an "older brother." However, I doubt that 
Gorby would care to write a Russian "Roots" to clarify the matter. 
</P>
<P>
KATHERYN GALLANT 
</P>
<P>
WEST COVINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
