<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: THE MIND OF SOUTH AFRICA BY ALLISTER SPARKS (ALFRED A. KNOPF: 
$24.95&amp; 424 PP.) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Richard Caplan 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"With the passion of a true patriot, Sparks looks forward to the day when his 
country ceases to be a symbol of racism, and instead of squandering its 
resources on hateful division, is able to tap its potential as an engine of 
African economic development." Richard Caplan 
</P>
</TEXT>
