<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMBASSIES IN CUBA SEALED OFF AS 9 MORE SEEK REFUGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAVANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cuban police sealed off the Canadian and West German embassies in Havana on 
Saturday and tightened a security cordon around the Spanish Embassy after nine 
more Cubans slipped through during the night and broke in. 
</P>
<P>
The latest arrivals brought to 18 the number of Cubans sheltering at the 
Spanish Embassy, further complicating a bitter diplomatic quarrel over the 
refugees that has seriously strained relations between Madrid and Havana. 
</P>
<P>
Another four Cubans are at the residence of the Italian ambassador. 
</P>
<P>
Fidel Castro's Communist government has been insisting that all asylum-seekers 
surrender to Cuban authorities without condition. The government has called all 
those who have gone into the Spanish, Czechoslovak and Italian embassies and 
diplomatic residences in recent days "scum" and habitual vagrants. 
</P>
