<HEADLINE>
<P>
8 CHILDREN AMONG 11 INJURED IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eleven people were injured, including eight children, when a car and a station 
wagon collided Saturday evening at the busy intersection of Rosecrans Avenue 
and Figueroa Street in Los Angeles, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Two of the adults were critically injured and one was listed in serious 
condition, city fire officials reported. 
</P>
<P>
All of the children were hospitalized but with only minor injuries, Los Angeles 
City Fire Department spokesman Greg Acevedo said. 
</P>
<P>
Names of the injured were not released. 
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred at 6:45 p.m. as a station wagon traveling southbound on 
Figueroa Street collided with a car turning west onto Rosecrans Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Police said at least seven children were traveling in the station wagon, all 
apparently of preschool age. None appeared to be wearing seatbelts or riding in 
protective car seats. 
</P>
<P>
Five rescue ambulances and two fire units responded to the crash and victims 
were rushed to Harbor-UCLA and Martin Luther King Jr./Drew medical centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072290-0136 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 250854 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 22, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
