<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGHLAND PARK WOMAN SETS HERSELF ON FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A distraught 35-year-old Highland Park woman set herself ablaze on a 
neighborhood street early Saturday morning, suffering third-degree burns on 90% 
of her body, a Los Angeles police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Horrified neighbors saw Louisa Jiminez of 5514 Marmion Way engulfed in flames 
about 6:15 a.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
One neighbor who ran to extinguish the flames with a garden hose told police 
that Jiminez tried to wave him away. 
</P>
<P>
Jiminez, a mother of three young children, was taken to Huntington Memorial 
Hospital in Pasadena and was in critical condition Saturday evening, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. John Johnston said Jiminez was apparently despondent and had asked her 
husband the night before to set her on fire to "purify" her body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
