SHY TOM SCORES VICTORY AT LAUREL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAUREL, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shy Tom, from the stable of North America's leading trainer, Wayne Lukas, edged 
Doc's Leader by a neck in the $162,950 Baltimore Budweiser Breeders' Cup at 
Laurel Race Course Saturday. 
