<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUL COSTS MI SELECTO WIN; ENTRYMATE IS GIVEN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ELMONT, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Angel Penna-trained entry of Montubio and Mi Selecto ran 1-2 in Saturday's 
$403,300 Brooklyn Handicap at Belmont Park, although investigation of a foul 
claim prompted stewards to switch the order of finish. 
</P>
<P>
Mi Selecto, ridden by Jerry Bailey, finished the 1 1/2 miles a head in front of 
Montubio, with Jacinto Vasquez in the saddle. 
</P>
<P>
Vasquez claimed foul against Mi Selecto, and patrol films used to decide the 
complaint showed Mi Selecto bearing out under left-handed whipping and impeding 
Montubio. 
</P>
<P>
De Roche, the odds-on favorite, was third in the seven-horse field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
