<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH BOB; 
</P>
<P>
MAN VS. MICROCHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I lost $130 Saturday when my key exacta horses, Might Be Right in the third 
race and Past Remembered in the ninth, each finished fifth. 
</P>
<P>
My bets for today are a $20 triple from Reason To Be, Forest Fairy and Sum 
Queen in the fourth to Paisano Pete in the fifth to Sea Cadet in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
Bob's Saturday Bankroll: $1,411 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's Loss: $130 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll: $1,281 
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK correctly picked Girl of France ($13.40) on top of his ninth race 
exacta, but put it with Past Remembered and lost $60. However, the computer 
retains a $439.50 lead -- a swing of more than $1,000 its way since June 27. 
</P>
<P>
SURELOCK's bet for today is $40 to win and $40 to place on Hot and Smoggy in 
the 10th race. 
</P>
<P>
Computer's Sat. Bankroll: $1,780.50 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's Loss: $60 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll: $1,720.50 
</P>
</TEXT>
