<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHY RUSH TO VEGAS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Am I missing something, somewhere, along the way? Admittedly, there are a lot 
of projects under way these days that I don't understand. Some of them are 
highly technical, and thus are beyond me. 
</P>
<P>
But there is one basically simple one that is nonetheless beyond my 
comprehension. 
</P>
<P>
Will somebody please tell me: What is the burning need -- or for that matter, 
any need at all -- for a high-speed rail line between Anaheim and Las Vegas? 
</P>
<P>
With so many really worthy projects that could better use the money, I have to 
ask: Who needs to get from Anaheim to Las Vegas -- or back -- in a hurry? For 
what reason? And if it's that important, why can't they do it by air? 
</P>
<P>
ALLYN M. SUFFENS 
