like states' rights and address the horrible drug problem in our nation." 
</P>
<P>
Opponent Tom DeLay (R-Tex.) objected to "sort of a blackmail attitude of 
withholding federal highway funds because states do not pass certain laws." 
</P>
<P>
A yes vote was for the amendment. 
</P>
