462 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY REPAIRS; 
</P>
<P>
ON THE ROAD; 
</P>
<P>
CALTRANS ISSUES ADVISORY ON THIS WEEK'S REPAIR SITES SO MOTORISTS CAN STEER 
CLEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Caltrans advises motorists that it plans the following freeway work in the 
Southeast and Long Beach area this week. Repair locations listed below are 
keyed to the nearest city or cities and are spotted on the map by number. 
</P>
<P>
ARTESIA FREEWAY (91) 
</P>
<P>
1. Bellflower /Cerritos: Eastbound No. 1 diamond lane; Woodruff Avenue to San 
Gabriel River Freeway (605); Tuesday, 8:30 a.m. to 1 p.m.; landscaping. 
</P>
<P>
2. Bellflower /Cerritos: Eastbound No. 6 lane; Woodruff Avenue to San Gabriel 
River Freeway (605); Wednesday, 8:30 a.m. to 1 p.m.; shoulder repair. 
</P>
<P>
HARBOR FREEWAY (110) 
</P>
<P>
3. San Pedro: Northbound No. 1 lane; Gaffey Street to Channel Street; Monday, 8 
a.m. to 2 p.m.; raised markers. 
</P>
<P>
4. San Pedro: Southbound alternating lanes; Channel Street to Gaffey Street; 
Tuesday, 9:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.; raised markers. 
</P>
<P>
5. San Pedro: Westbound No. 3 lane, Harbor Boulevard to Terminal Island 
separation, Harbor Boulevard on-ramp and westbound Terminal Island connector to 
northbound Harbor Freeway (110); Wednesday, 9:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m.; raised 
markers. 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH FREEWAY (710) 
</P>
